+++++++++++++++
+ Metal/Bercy +
+++++++++++++++

@Node Metal_Bercy "Metallica at Bercy ( Paris ) : 16/09/1996"

Monday, the 16th of  september  1996. Today  is a very good day. I am
going  to Paris  to see one of  my favourite bands : Metallica. It is
their  second gig at Bercy... I went  there 'coz the  belgian gig was
sold-out some days after the beginning of the tickets' sale.

At 10.15 am, I went  to Liège with my friend to take the bus to go to
Paris but also to  buy some  tickets  for the concerts of @{"Soundgarden" Link SoundInfo}
and @{"Kiss" Link KissInfo} in Belgium ( don't miss the report in a next edition ).

The real  departure  took place at 12.00 am. My friend met someone he
has not  seen  since  2 years ( You  must  go to Paris to meet an old
friend... The world is closer ! ). After  some  stops, we finally are
in Paris. It's 06.15 pm. Everyone  was  wearing  a Metallica T-Shirt.
Are  they  in  town  tonight for  something ??? We are checked by the
security guards, our ticket is teared in  two and  we enter the Bercy
arena.

The scene was gigantic. Is was in the center of the arena and divided
into 2 parts, forming a huge 8. On my  right, the  battery was in the
center, in the middle was the technical crew and on my left, a second
stage with two metallic arms down. At each corner of the right stage,
there was an articulated arm with light at the end.

Just the time  to find a good  place, buy some merchandising ( french
prices  are very  high ! Almost  50 % higher  than  Belgium ), listen
to the new album of @{"Rage Against The Machine" Link RageInfo} in loop ( it was getting
boring at the end ! ), and the show was about to begin.
The  support  band  was @{"Corrosion of Conformity" Link CorrInfo}. Their gig started at
07.20 pm ( ended at 07.55 pm ). It was good, the  sound was sometimes
crap, but it was loud  enough to  please me. The public welcomed them
very well. I think they must be glad !

We  had  to  wait  until 08.45 pm to finally see the band. The lights
were  yet on and  Jason Newsted ( bass ) came  up running  around the
stage,  followed  by  James  Hetfield ( vocals  and   guitars ), Kirk
Hammett ( guitars ) was  already on stage. The last Metallica dude to
come was Lars Ulrich under thousands of bestial howls.
The  began  the  show with  a " So Fucking  What ? " with  lights yet
on !!! No time to rust ! They continued with " Creeping death " after
the lights  were  turned of. The lightshow is amazing  with the  four
articulated arms.
James asked  to  the  crowd : " You  want heavy ? We give you heavy "
before  playing  a " Sad  But  True " louder  than  ever, followed by
" Ain't My Bitch ", first  song  from the new album. The new material
works  very  well  live. Load  can  seem  quite  soft sometimes, it's
terrific on stage. Metallica is still Metallica, believe me.
It's time now for some Disco. The  Metalli-Disco  is playing a mix of
this 70's sound  under  the cries of the fans. Place for real music :
they fixed that mistake with an ultra-speeded " Whiplash ".
Tempo was slowing with " Bleeding me " and getting harder with " King
Nothing " where  the  other articulated  arms  on the left stage were
lifted. Lights  were  red and a huge smoke was spreaded. Some strobo-
scopic efects added more atmosphere.
The special effects continued with a classic song of the band " One "
and some explosions on stage. Very great !!!

James Hetfield told that  they were going to play a very new song due
to be released on the  next album. I couldn't  believe my hears. They
were about to  play the  already  famous " Devil Dance ". I must  say
that this song is really loud. Heavier than " Sad But True " in fact.

The band  took  a moment  to rust  while Jason  was playing some bass
soli. For a Maiden fan, it was a great time to hear " Hallowed Be Thy
Name " played on  the bass. Kirk  came up  and  played " My Friend Of
Misery " with Jason. They ended this short  break with " Sanitarium "
where Lars came on stage on his second drums on the left stage.

Second part of the  gig began  quietly  with " Nothing Else Matters "
and the first single of Load : " Until It Sleeps ".
Things get louder with " For Whom  The  Bell Tolls " and " Wherever I
May Roam ". After that, they did an excellent " Fade To Black ".

James  asked  to  the  crowd  who has " Kill 'em All " and " Ride The
Lightning ". It  was to  introduce a long medley of these two albums.
This medley was composed by : - Ride The Lightning
                              - No Remorse
                              - Hit The Light
                              - Seek And Destroy
                              - Fight Fire With Fire
During  this masterpiece, the public reaction was huge. Many slammers
and others gave a lot of work to the Order Service !

It was the end of the show, but they came back after the acclamations
of the public.  Just the time to change the instruments ( and to play
some  accords   of  Wrathchild ( Maiden ) ),  they  played " Shortest
Straw " ( it was a long time we heard this song live ), the very good
" Master Of Puppets " and finally " Enter Sandman ".

The  end  was  very  near. Metallica  managed to end their  show with
a lot of effects. I don't want to give you  those details because you
must  see  it  with  your  own  eyes. If you  know what happenend, it
wouldn't be  the same. I must say  that it is  wonderful and don't be
afraid, they're professional !

The  final part was  arrived and they played some reprises, very well
indeed. We have heard : - Last Caress ( Danzig )
                        - Breadfan
                        - Overkill ( Motörhead )

The show ended at 11:05 pm. So, the  conclusion  of this show is that
since 4  years ( the first time I  saw them ), Metallica  is always a
monster  on  stage. The  put  a lot of  energy, sweat, and passion in
everything they do. I really  encourage you  to see them if they come
near your town ( and I'm sure they will ).

SET-LIST
~~~~~~~~

