@endnode

++++++++++++++++++++++++
+ Soundgarden / Forest +
++++++++++++++++++++++++

@Node Sound_Forest "Soundgarden at Forest ( Brussels ) : 10/10/1996"

I have  discovered Soundarden recently  and I must say that this band
has pleased me wiht their music. I think that the comparison with Led
Zeppelin is  not usurped. So I decided  to see them in concert with a
friend.

The support bands were Eleven  and Moby. The first was unknown for me
and the band was  a trio : 1 drummer, 1 guitarist, 1 keyboard/singer.
The singer was a women, her voice was nice. No bass guitar : the bass
was made  with the keyboard  while playing some melodies and singing,
damn !, it's hard...

Moby came after it. Ah Moby ! I had the occasion to see him this year
at  the  Torhout/Werchter festival. This  time, no  techno, only good
Rock. We have heard his famous  reprise of Paranoid ( Black Sabbath )
played in 1 minute. This show was great.

Third part of the event, Soundgarden came. It's the first time that I
assist  to a concert  being so  calm. I was  sitting and enjoying the
show. I must say that I'm not  so big  and I hate hurt my neck trying
to see something.
The show : well, it  was huge... Chris Cornell  is a very good singer
on albums, but on the  very first songs, his voice was bad. You might
have said he was sick. But after it, everything went OK until the end
of the show. 
They  have  alterned atmospheric  songs ( Boot Camp ) with  more hard
pieces ( Rusty Cage ).
At the middle of the show, the band except the singer left the stage.
Chris  staid with  his guitar  and began a solo version of Black Hole
Sun, adding another dimension at the song.

I am pleased  to have seen them. This  show was nice although we were
tired ( so  tired  that  my  friend fell  asleep  during  the slowest
songs !!! ).

Set List ( incomplete... excuse me )
~~~~~~~~

- Spoonman
-
- Let Me Drown
- Pretty Nose
- Burden In My Hand
- My Wave
- Ty Cobb
- An Unkind
- Fell On Black Days
-
-
- Boot Camp
- Rusty Cage
- Black Hole Sun ( Solo singer with his guitar )
- Dusty
- Switch Opens
- Blow Up The Outside World
- Search And Destroy
- 
- No Attention
- Jesus Christ Pose

