####################
# Albums to listen #
####################

@Node Albums "Albums to listen"

@{b}My Dying Bride : Like Gods Of The Sun@{ub}

This  album is  THE album of  the month. I have  discovered "My Dying
Bride" last year with the show of  Iron Maiden. They were the support
band and I must say that I founded  this kind of music quite strange.
For those who don't  know it : imagine a mix  between a slow and dark
Heavy  Metal with  some classical  music ( violins ). This is special
the first time you hear it but it is magic.
So I saw their new album last week and  I decided to buy it. This new
CD is marvelous. The  atmospheres  are very dark  and deeply sad. The
violin adds  something gipsy. There  also is keyboards  finishing  to
create  this  atmosphere. The  guitars are  very  present  and heavy.
The  way  the  songs  are  created is also disappointing : you have a
certain tempo during 1 or 2 minutes  and after it, a break comes with
a louder  tempo before  speeding up. I like  because it  adds another
depth to the song.
I strongly encourage you to listen this album.

My quote : 9/10


@{b}Iron Maiden : Best Of The Beast@{ub}

Maiden  has  decided to  edit a best of. It coincides with their 20th
anniversary. As usual with Maiden, the  packaging is excellent and it
will be declined in 4 (!) different ways.
- A double Digipack CD with a 60 pages booklet
- A quadruple  LP with a 40  pages  booklet and containing the famous
  "Soundhouse Tapes"
- A double CD
- A simple CD
- And A Video Tape

I have bought  the limited double digipack  edition. The packaging is
nice and  the booklet  is really well-made. There  is a load of infos
about the band ( everything you need to know ).
The more  important  things are the music. All the classics of Maiden
are here : Iron Maiden, The  Trooper, The  Clairvoyant, Running Free,
The Number Of The Beast, and many  more. All the eras of the band are
depicted. You  will also  find the  very first  live  song with Blaze
Bailey. It is "Afraid To Shoot Strangers" and it is a good song. 

Beeing  personaly  a  great  fan of Iron Maiden, this album is a must
have for me. I collect everything I can  find on  them and I must buy
the 4 LP version very soon because of the simple fact that the Sound-
house Tapes are present on the discs !

Everyone who wants to know a little more about Maiden should buy this
album. It is a good representation of what the band is.

My quote : 8/10

@endnode


####################
# News and rumours #
####################

@Node News "News and rumours"

@{b}Machine Head@{ub}

Their  new  album  will  be  out next  january. It's titled "The More
Things Change". It was  due to  be out  this october  but  because of
mixing problems, it has been postponed until january.

@{b}Trent Reznor@{ub}

NIN  should  compose  the soundtrack of "Quake" the sequel of Doom on
PC. The band  has also  composed  some tracks for the new David Lynch
movie "Lost Highway".

@{b}Metallica@{ub}

They are 3 times platinum in the USA ( more than 3 millions of copies
sold ) with  their  last  album "Load". The "Black  Album" is 9 times
platinum !

@{b}Kiss@{ub}

Guitarist Bruce  Kulick and drummer  Eric Singer have definitely left
the band.

@{b}Pearl Jam@{ub}

They have only (!) sold 367 000 copies of "No Code" in the first week
in the States. It's the half of their last album "Vitalogy" ( 877 000
copies ) and "VS" ( 955 000 copies ). Times are hard !!!

@{b}Marylin Manson@{ub}

The  new album of  the  completely  mad singer  is titled "AntiChrist
Superstar".

@{b}Smashing Pumpkins@{ub}

They have had 8 MTV Music Video awards last 4th september :
- Best band video : Tonight, Tonight
- Breakthrough video : Tonight, Tonight
- Best realisation : Tonight, Tonight
- Best alternative video : 1979
- Best artistic direction : Tonight, Tonight
- Best special effects :Tonight, Tonight
- Best photography : Tonight, Tonight
- Best video of the year : Tonight, Tonight

@{b}Van Halen@{ub}

We said you last edition  that Sammy was out and that Dave was in. It
is not  true now ! Dave  is for a second  time out. He has decided to
leave VH... 
